    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey so im buying a house in austin and the seller is asking for earnest money but the title company says it has to go into an escrow account first. why can't i just give it to them or keep it in my own account until we close? seems like a lot of extra steps.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Earnest money, a good-faith deposit, is a necessary part of the transaction, and it's usually handled through an escrow account for security. The title company is right to insist on it; it protects everyone involved, including you, from any unexpected issues. Think of it like this: the earnest money is a small, protected pool of money that the title company holds until everything lines up perfectly. It's a standard procedure for keeping the whole deal safe from any unexpected surprises.",
