    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i'm just worried about the \"holding\" part. it feels like i have no control over it once it's in their hands. is there any way the title company could just... mismanage it or someone could steal it out of that account? how do i know it's actually being guarded properly?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Don't let the thought of a stolen deposit make you nervous, though, because the title company, even if they are just a service provider, has to follow strict regulations. Escrow accounts are not just loose piles of cash; they are legally mandated to be held in a secure, separate account, often managed by a neutral third party or a specialized escrow service.\n\nYou need to look for documentation that outlines exactly *how* the funds are being held and what the terms are for release. It's a formality, but you should be able to ask the title company for details on their security protocols. If you are truly worried, you can ask them to show you the escrow agreement or the specific account details.",
